Sytrime Dervisholli
Executive Director

Sytrime Dervisholli

Prefabricated Construction Cluster of Kosova

Session: Wood-Metal/Construction Innovative Transformation and R&D-based Challenges

Sytrime is a senior expert on economic development and international trade, with more than 15 years of experience in both the public and private sector. She played a pivotal role in shaping policies for domestic and international trade, fostering private sector growth. She specializes in trade and economic related initiatives, leveraging her role as a former CEFTA Contact Point, trade negotiator and policy maker.

As an author, she has made significant contributions through impactful articles, including the Guide for Foreign Investors.

Sytrime currently serves as a certified Trainer on Circular Economy, certified Expert on ESG, and as a Consultant at the World Bank Group/IFC, where she actively contributes to the strengthening of the private sector initiatives and state institutions specializing in trade.

Sytrime obtained a degree from the Faculty of Economics at the University of Prishtina and Master degree on Public Administration from Rochester Institute of Technology in Kosovo.

Company Profile

The Prefabricated Constructions Cluster was established in 2023 to serve as the common voice of the industry of manufacturers of buildings and prefabricated products, promoting the common interests of businesses in the field and individuals from these fields.
The Prefab Constructions Cluster aims to increase the competitiveness of the prefabricated construction sector in the regional and international markets.
The Prefab Construction Cluster is committed to improving the business environment for the sector and promoting the industry’s contribution to economic growth and development in Kosovo.
The Prefab Constructions Cluster aims to participate in the development and implementation of production and export policies in Kosovo, helping the government and institutions of Kosovo to develop these policies according to contemporary trends in order to grow and develop the country’s economy.
The Prefab Constructions Cluster will be committed to empowering the community of businesses in the development and advancement of products and services in the prefab construction sector through academic cooperation with academic institutions and other relevant institutions, through the promotion of innovation, research, cooperation, development of skills and creating bridges for investors.
